Ah, world, what lessons you prepare for us, 
even in the leafless winter, 
even in the ashy city.
I am thinking now
of grief, and of getting past it; 
I feel my boots
trying to leave the ground, 
I feel my heart
pumping hard. I want 
to think again of dangerous and noble things.
I want to be light and frolicsome.
I want to be improbable beautiful and afraid of nothing, 
as though I had wings. —Mary Oliver.  Happy Winter Solstice! Even in the darkness, may you feel light and frolicsome, and may you be afraid of nothing. 😘

Happy #GivingTuesday. Today I am teaming up with @plancanada and taking the time to give thanks and reflect on what I’m truly grateful for. Education. Education is one necessity we sometimes take for granted, yet 263 million children around the world are out of school. The good news is that together we can make a difference. By giving the gift of school essentials through @plancanada’s Gifts of Hope, you can not only provide textbooks and pencils, but also help children receive education in emergency situations and support programs to reduce school violence, improve school hygiene and train more teachers. I have seen first hand the difference this program makes in the lives of children and their families. Click the link in my bio to learn more. Let’s take a break from the frenzy of this holiday season and spread a little love together.❤️ #GiftsofHope. P.S. This is the perfect gift for that special someone in your life who is impossible to shop for. And it’s super easy. You’re welcome. ✔️🤪😘🎁

My daughter and I are celebrating our favorite month of the year with some guilt free screen time. @Vooks is an online platform that brings books to life with animated illustrations, read along text and narrated story. It’s kid safe for ages 2-8, and a wonderful way to unlock the magic of reading! Reading to my daughters has always been one of my favorite ways to spend mother daughter time throughout the years. Vooks gives us a unique way to connect through reading, and she gets to share her favorite books with me. You can follow @vooks for new releases + exciting updates. And for  a limited time, Vooks and I are teaming up to provide all parents and guardians in the U.S. free Vooks for 3 months! @Vooks wants to thank all of the incredible parents and guardians who are loving and supporting children, plus teaching them the love of reading.  P.S. If you’d like a suggestion, check out one of our all time favorite titles “A Sick Day For Amos McGee”, a story of kindness and empathy that we have enjoyed over and over and over again. Click link in my bio for free Vooks access! #vookspartner #raisingreaders #sponsored

It’s #DayoftheGirl! Let’s hear it for the girls...girls like Loretta who have the inherent power within to be who and what they want to be. Every day, girls around the world are denied the opportunity to learn. Globally, more than 130 million girls are not attending school. We can no longer accept this as ‘normal’. It’s time to #DefyNormal and make sure that girls have access to the quality education and support they need. How will you use your power to help girls unleash theirs? Let me know in the comments below! 
And for all my friends  in Canada, you can join @PlanCanada today to help send 100 girls in Uganda to school. Text: POWER to 30333 to donate $10 today. ❤️👍🏻💪🏼
